author: dberlin
msg: Add IPV6 listen support to svnserve
* Makefile.in: Add svncheck6
* subversion/svnserve/main.c (main): Get listen host info first,
then use resulting family in the socket creation.

author: dberlin
msg: Use apr_uri_parse to parse svn urls, since it knows
how to handle ipv6 addresses.
Modify host lookup to allow lookup of ipv6 addresses,
and use result of address info getting to determine
what type of socket to create.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_client/client.c (parse_tunnel):
Copied pieces from parse_url to parse out tunnel specification.
(ra_svn_open): Use apr_uri_parse + parse_tunnel, not parse_url, to parse
the url given to us.
(make_connection): Use APR_UNSPEC, which will determine the
family for us.  Also, use the resulting family as the family of
the socket we create.
